desc:precision PCM
author:acer bt and claude
version:2.12
tags:bitcrusher distortion retro samplerate
changelog:
	v2.12
	no functional changes from v2.11 / v2.1
	documents the v3.x experiment and why it was abandoned:
	  attempted to unify all modes under a polyphase fractional-delay FIR
	  reconstruction pipeline, with the goal of making capture timing phase-
	  coherent with the anti-alias filter across modes 0-3, and replacing the
	  FIR band-limited mode's static lowpass with true bandlimited decimation.
	  problems encountered and why each was abandoned:
	  - phase-coherent capture for modes 0-3: introduced AM sidebands that were
	    absent in v2.1. the sidebands in v2.1 modes 0-3 come from the decimation
	    grid itself and are expected/authentic; the new ones came from asymmetry
	    between the fixed Blackman window and the shifting sinc center at non-zero
	    frac values. reverted — IIR pre-filter does not need phase alignment with
	    the capture moment to suppress aliasing effectively.
	  - true polyphase FIR decimation for mode 4: produced periodic energy at
	    exactly the target sample rate, confirmed by ring mod test (8001hz ring
	    mod against 8k target -> 2hz beat; 8002hz -> 4hz beat). multiple attempts
	    to fix the frac mapping and normalization failed to eliminate the artifact.
	    root cause: any discrete capture/hold mechanism creates a decimation grid
	    that ring-mod tests will find, regardless of how clean the interpolation is.
	  - the v2.1 FIR mode is technically not doing true decimation (it filters
	    every host sample with no sample discard), but this is exactly why it
	    passes the ring mod test cleanly — there is no decimation grid to beat
	    against. it correctly represents what ideal band-limiting at the target
	    rate sounds like, which is the point of the mode.
	  - hybrid IIR fallback below 8kHz: added then removed. user is expected to
	    choose appropriate settings (IIR band-limited + steep IIR pre-filter) for
	    extreme low rates rather than having the plugin silently change behavior.
	  conclusion: v2.1 architecture is correct for the goals of this plugin.
	  FIR band-limited as a static per-sample lowpass is the right design for a
	  "what would ideal reconstruction sound like" reference mode. IIR pre-filter
	  with steep rolloff is the right tool for alias suppression at low target rates.
	v2.1
	fixed FIR band-limited mode to eliminate AM sidebands
	FIR mode now filters directly at target Nyquist without sample-and-hold
	modes 0-3 retain authentic capture/hold behavior with expected artifacts
	fixed IIR band-limited mode to apply post bit-crush (filters quantization)
	v2.0
	fixed cubic interpolation to use proper 4-point calculation with look-ahead
	added FIR filter option with 128-tap windowed-sinc and Blackman window

about:
	This effect started as an attempt to make a bitcrusher with detailed controls, but has since become a pcm output simulator. It acts like a regular bitcrusher in that it can do bit reduction and bad resampling, but it can also do a lot more. Below is a list of the available parameters and there functions.
	sample rate (Hz): sets the rate that the plugin will resample audio to. The default is 44100 Hz, and it can go from 100 Hz to 192000 Hz.
	interpolation mode: sets the interpolation mode used when processing samples. The default is set to sample and hold, for retro purposes, but it also includes linear, cubic, and 2 band limited modes. Band limited iir combines cubic interpolation with a low pass filter just before the final output, to get as close to high quality reconstruction as possible. If you need possibly more accurate sounding reconstruction, you can use fir mode instead, which filters to nyquist using a 128 tap fir filter. Note that cubic and band-limited iir modes add 1 sample of latency for proper 4-point interpolation.
	prefilter (antialiasing): this applies low pass filtering before the down sampling step, to reduce frequencies that would cause fold over aliasing. It's disabled by default. You can choose between IIR (Butterworth) or FIR (linear-phase) modes. IIR mode has minimal latency but gentler rolloff. FIR mode adds ~64 samples of latency but provides brick-wall filtering with no phase distortion.
	prefilter rolloff (dB/oct): sets the rolloff rate for the IIR prefilter, which determines how much frequencies above the prefilter frequency are attenuated. 12 dB per octave is default, it can go in 12 dB steps all the way to 72 dB per octave. Do note that you will need steeper rolloffs for antialiasing at lower samplerates if you want it to sound clean. This setting only affects IIR mode.
	prefilter quality: controls the tradeoff between bandwidth preservation and aliasing prevention when using iir mode. Maximum Bandwidth gets closest to Nyquist (may allow slight aliasing at extreme low rates), Adaptive automatically adjusts based on target sample rate (recommended), Clean uses conservative filtering that guarantees minimal aliasing at most rates, Ultra Clean uses very conservative filtering for maximum artifact elimination at extreme low rates. Use Maximum Bandwidth for transparent resampling at normal rates, Adaptive for general use, Clean for working below 8 kHz, or Ultra Clean when absolute purity is required at very low rates (trades significant bandwidth for complete artifact removal). This setting only affects IIR mode.
	band limit rolloff (dB/oct): similar to the rolloff for the prefilter, but it affects the rolloff rate for the band limiting filter used just before the output when interpolation mode is set to iir band limited. It defaults to 48 dB per octave, and goes from 12 to 72 dB per octave in 12 dB steps. This setting only affects IIR mode.
	band limit quality: controls reconstruction filter behavior in band-limited mode when using IIR filters. Maximum Bandwidth preserves the most high frequency content (may have slight artifacts at extreme low rates), Adaptive automatically adjusts for cleaner reconstruction at low rates while staying aggressive at normal rates (recommended), Clean uses conservative filtering for artifact-free reconstruction at most rates, Ultra Clean uses very conservative filtering for maximum purity at extreme low rates. Use Maximum Bandwidth for professional quality resampling above 8 kHz, Adaptive for general use, Clean for rates below 8 kHz, or Ultra Clean for complete artifact elimination at very low rates. Note: Clean and Ultra Clean modes automatically use linear interpolation below 8 kHz for cleaner results. This setting only affects IIR mode.
	bit depth crushing (enabled/ disabled): determines if the bit reduction component of the effect is on or off. It defaults to off.
	bit depth: sets the target bit depth to crush to. Default is 16, and it can go from 1 to 24 bit. Lower bit depths introduce more noise into the signal and lower dynamic range.
	crush mode (gated/ no gate): determines if the bit crushing gates the output, or keeps a constant noise floor below the sound at lower bit depths. Default is no gate.
	dither type (none/ rpdf/ tpdf): controls the type of dithering applied before bit reduction. Dithering converts harsh quantization distortion into smooth random noise, which is especially noticeable at lower bit depths. None disables dithering (default), RPDF (rectangular probability density function) applies basic random dither, and TPDF (triangular probability density function) applies higher quality dither that's less audible. TPDF is recommended for cleaner results.
	dither amount (%): sets the intensity of the dither signal from 0 to 100 percent. At 100% (default), dithering is applied at the proper mathematical level for the target bit depth. Lower values reduce the dither noise but may allow some quantization distortion to remain. This control is mainly for creative/experimental purposes - for proper PCM reconstruction, keep it at 100%.
	dither silence cutoff: when enabled (default), dithering will not be applied to signals below -96 dB to avoid adding noise to silent passages. When disabled, dithering is always applied when enabled (mathematically accurate). Disable this for archival/mastering work where absolute accuracy is required.
	isolation filter (high pass): this switch toggles the state of a high pass filter which can be used to filter for just aliasing/ sample and hold artafacts. It defaults to off. This filter is IIR-only for low-latency artifact analysis.
	isolation filter rolloff (dB/oct): determines how much frequencies below the cutoff point of the isolation filter are roled off. It defaults to 12 dB per octave, and has the same value choices as the other filters in this plugin.
	output gain (dB): sets the final output level after processing. Default is 0 dB, and it ranges from -24 to 24 dB.
	output mode (stereo/mono): sets if the plugin outputs in stereo, or sums both channels to mono before outputting. Default is stereo

slider1:44100<100,192000,10>Sample Rate (Hz)
slider2:0<0,4,1{Sample & Hold,Linear,Cubic,Band-Limited (IIR),Band-Limited (FIR)}>Interpolation Mode
slider3:0<0,2,1{Disabled,IIR (Butterworth),FIR (Linear Phase)}>Pre-Filter (Anti-Aliasing)
slider4:0<1,6,1{12 dB/oct,24 dB/oct,36 dB/oct,48 dB/oct,60 dB/oct,72 dB/oct}>Pre-Filter Rolloff (IIR)
slider5:1<0,3,1{Maximum Bandwidth,Adaptive,Clean,Ultra Clean}>Pre-Filter Quality
slider6:3<1,6,1{12 dB/oct,24 dB/oct,36 dB/oct,48 dB/oct,60 dB/oct,72 dB/oct}>Band-Limit Rolloff (IIR)
slider7:1<0,3,1{Maximum Bandwidth,Adaptive,Clean,Ultra Clean}>Band-Limit Quality (IIR)
slider8:0<0,1,1{Disabled,Enabled}>Bit Depth Crushing
slider9:16<1,24,1>Bit Depth
slider10:0<0,2,1{No Gate,Gated}>Crush Mode
slider11:0<0,2,1{None,RPDF,TPDF}>Dither Type
slider12:100<0,100,1>Dither Amount (%)
slider13:1<0,1,1{Disabled,Enabled}>Dither Silence Cutoff
slider14:0<0,1,1{Disabled,Enabled}>Isolation Filter (HPF - IIR Only)
slider15:0<1,6,1{12 dB/oct,24 dB/oct,36 dB/oct,48 dB/oct,60 dB/oct,72 dB/oct}>Isolation Filter Rolloff
slider16:0<-24,24,0.1>Output Gain (dB)
slider17:0<0,1,1{Stereo,Mono}>Output Mode

in_pin:left input
in_pin:right input
out_pin:left output
out_pin:right output

@init
initialized = 0;

// Filter state memory
fir_pre_buffer_l = 200;
fir_pre_buffer_r = 328;
fir_band_buffer_l = 500;
fir_band_buffer_r = 628;
fir_tap_count = 128;
fir_buffer_pos = 0;

// Sample rate reduction variables
phase_accum_l = phase_accum_r = 0;
held_l = held_r = 0;
prev_held_l = prev_held_r = 0;
pprev_held_l = pprev_held_r = 0;
next_held_l = next_held_r = 0;

pi = $pi;

// Math helper functions
function asinh(x) ( log(x + sqrt(x * x + 1)); );
function sinh(x) ( (exp(x) - exp(-x)) / 2; );
function cosh(x) ( (exp(x) + exp(-x)) / 2; );

// FIR lowpass filter using windowed-sinc
function fir_lowpass(input, buffer_base, cutoff_freq)
local(i, sum, n, window, sinc_val, normalized_freq, coeff, coeff_sum, half_taps, current_pos)
(
  buffer_base[fir_buffer_pos] = input;
  sum = 0;
  coeff_sum = 0;
  normalized_freq = cutoff_freq / srate;
  half_taps = fir_tap_count / 2;
  
  i = 0;
  loop(fir_tap_count,
    n = i - half_taps;
    n == 0 ? (
      sinc_val = 2 * normalized_freq;
    ) : (
      sinc_val = sin(2 * pi * normalized_freq * n) / (pi * n);
    );
    window = 0.42 - 0.5 * cos(2 * pi * i / (fir_tap_count - 1)) + 
             0.08 * cos(4 * pi * i / (fir_tap_count - 1));
    coeff = sinc_val * window;
    coeff_sum += coeff;
    current_pos = (fir_buffer_pos - i + fir_tap_count) % fir_tap_count;
    sum += buffer_base[current_pos] * coeff;
    i += 1;
  );
  
  coeff_sum > 0.0001 ? sum / coeff_sum : input;
);

// IIR lowpass filter stage (Butterworth)
function filter_stage_lp(input, mem_base, stage, channel, freq, total_stages)
local(base, w, cosw, sinw, alpha, b0, b1, b2, a1, a2, x1, x2, y1, y2, output, norm)
(
  base = mem_base + (stage - 1) * 8 + channel * 4;
  x1 = base[0]; x2 = base[1]; y1 = base[2]; y2 = base[3];
  w = 2 * pi * freq / srate;
  cosw = cos(w); sinw = sin(w);
  alpha = sinw / 1.414213562373095;
  b0 = (1 - cosw) / 2; b1 = 1 - cosw; b2 = b0;
  a1 = -2 * cosw; a2 = 1 - alpha;
  norm = 1 / (1 + alpha);
  b0 *= norm; b1 *= norm; b2 *= norm; a1 *= norm; a2 *= norm;
  output = b0*input + b1*x1 + b2*x2 - a1*y1 - a2*y2;
  base[0] = input; base[1] = x1; base[2] = output; base[3] = y1;
  output;
);

// IIR highpass filter stage (Butterworth)
function filter_stage_hp(input, mem_base, stage, channel, freq, total_stages)
local(base, w, cosw, sinw, alpha, b0, b1, b2, a1, a2, x1, x2, y1, y2, output, norm)
(
  base = mem_base + (stage - 1) * 8 + channel * 4;
  x1 = base[0]; x2 = base[1]; y1 = base[2]; y2 = base[3];
  w = 2 * pi * freq / srate;
  cosw = cos(w); sinw = sin(w);
  alpha = sinw / 1.414213562373095;
  b0 = (1 + cosw) / 2; b1 = -(1 + cosw); b2 = b0;
  a1 = -2 * cosw; a2 = 1 - alpha;
  norm = 1 / (1 + alpha);
  b0 *= norm; b1 *= norm; b2 *= norm; a1 *= norm; a2 *= norm;
  output = b0*input + b1*x1 + b2*x2 - a1*y1 - a2*y2;
  base[0] = input; base[1] = x1; base[2] = output; base[3] = y1;
  output;
);

// Bit depth crushing function
function bit_crush(input, bits, gated)
local(levels, step, crushed, gate_threshold)
(
  bits <= 1 ? (
    input >= 0 ? 1 : -1;
  ) : (
    levels = pow(2, bits);
    step = 2.0 / levels;
    crushed = floor((input + 1.0) / step) * step - 1.0;
    gated ? (
      gate_threshold = step * 0.5;
      abs(input) < gate_threshold ? 0 : crushed;
    ) : crushed;
  );
);

// Dither application
function apply_dither(input, bits, dtype, amount)
local(lsb, r1, r2, dither_signal)
(
  bits <= 1 || dtype == 0 ? input : (
    lsb = 1.0 / pow(2, bits);
    dtype == 1 ? (
      dither_signal = (rand() - 0.5) * lsb * amount;
    ) : (
      r1 = rand() - 0.5; r2 = rand() - 0.5;
      dither_signal = (r1 + r2) * lsb * amount;
    );
    input + dither_signal;
  );
);

// Linear interpolation
function linear_interp(frac, prev, curr)
(
  prev + (curr - prev) * frac
);

// Cubic interpolation (4-point)
function cubic_interp(frac, pprev, prev, curr, next)
local(a0, a1, a2, a3, f2, f3)
(
  f2 = frac * frac; f3 = f2 * frac;
  a0 = -0.5 * pprev + 1.5 * prev - 1.5 * curr + 0.5 * next;
  a1 = pprev - 2.5 * prev + 2 * curr - 0.5 * next;
  a2 = -0.5 * pprev + 0.5 * curr;
  a3 = prev;
  a0 * f3 + a1 * f2 + a2 * frac + a3
);

@slider
slider1_raw = slider1;
target_rate = max(100, min(slider1, srate));
interp_mode = floor(slider2);

prefilter = slider3;
pre_stages = slider4 + 1;
pre_quality = slider5;
bandlimit_stages = slider6 + 1;
bandlimit_quality = slider7;
btcrush = slider8;
bit_depth = max(1, min(slider9, 24));
crushgate = slider10;
dither_type = slider11;
dither_amount = slider12 / 100.0;
dither_silence_cutoff = slider13;
postfilter = slider14;
isolation_stages = slider15 + 1;
gain = pow(10, slider16 / 20);
mono_mode = slider17;

// Calculate filter frequencies
rate_factor = target_rate / 44100;
rate_factor < 0.18 ? (
  adaptive_scale = 0.88 - (0.18 - rate_factor) * 0.4;
) : (
  adaptive_scale = 1.0;
);

// Pre-filter frequency calculation
pre_quality == 0 ? (
  pre_stages == 1 ? correction = 1.03 :
  pre_stages == 2 ? correction = 1.06 :
  pre_stages == 3 ? correction = 1.08 :
  pre_stages == 4 ? correction = 1.09 :
  pre_stages == 5 ? correction = 1.10 :
  correction = 1.11;
) : pre_quality == 1 ? (
  pre_stages == 1 ? base_correction = 1.03 :
  pre_stages == 2 ? base_correction = 1.06 :
  pre_stages == 3 ? base_correction = 1.08 :
  pre_stages == 4 ? base_correction = 1.09 :
  pre_stages == 5 ? base_correction = 1.10 :
  base_correction = 1.11;
  correction = base_correction * adaptive_scale;
) : pre_quality == 2 ? (
  pre_stages == 1 ? correction = 0.98 :
  pre_stages == 2 ? correction = 1.00 :
  pre_stages == 3 ? correction = 1.01 :
  pre_stages == 4 ? correction = 1.02 :
  pre_stages == 5 ? correction = 1.03 :
  correction = 1.04;
) : (
  pre_stages == 1 ? correction = 0.84 :
  pre_stages == 2 ? correction = 0.88 :
  pre_stages == 3 ? correction = 0.92 :
  pre_stages == 4 ? correction = 0.94 :
  pre_stages == 5 ? correction = 0.96 :
  correction = 0.97;
);
nyquist_freq = target_rate * 0.5 * correction;
nyquist_freq = min(nyquist_freq, srate * 0.475);

// Band-limit frequency calculation
bandlimit_quality == 0 ? (
  bandlimit_stages == 1 ? bl_correction = 1.06 :
  bandlimit_stages == 2 ? bl_correction = 1.08 :
  bandlimit_stages == 3 ? bl_correction = 1.09 :
  bandlimit_stages == 4 ? bl_correction = 1.10 :
  bandlimit_stages == 5 ? bl_correction = 1.11 :
  bl_correction = 1.12;
) : bandlimit_quality == 1 ? (
  bandlimit_stages == 1 ? bl_base_correction = 1.06 :
  bandlimit_stages == 2 ? bl_base_correction = 1.08 :
  bandlimit_stages == 3 ? bl_base_correction = 1.09 :
  bandlimit_stages == 4 ? bl_base_correction = 1.10 :
  bandlimit_stages == 5 ? bl_base_correction = 1.11 :
  bl_base_correction = 1.12;
  bl_correction = bl_base_correction * adaptive_scale;
) : bandlimit_quality == 2 ? (
  bandlimit_stages == 1 ? bl_correction = 0.98 :
  bandlimit_stages == 2 ? bl_correction = 1.00 :
  bandlimit_stages == 3 ? bl_correction = 1.02 :
  bandlimit_stages == 4 ? bl_correction = 1.03 :
  bandlimit_stages == 5 ? bl_correction = 1.04 :
  bl_correction = 1.05;
) : (
  bandlimit_stages == 1 ? bl_correction = 0.88 :
  bandlimit_stages == 2 ? bl_correction = 0.92 :
  bandlimit_stages == 3 ? bl_correction = 0.95 :
  bandlimit_stages == 4 ? bl_correction = 0.97 :
  bandlimit_stages == 5 ? bl_correction = 0.98 :
  bl_correction = 0.99;
);
bandlimit_freq = target_rate * 0.5 * bl_correction;
bandlimit_freq = min(bandlimit_freq, srate * 0.475);

@sample
input_l = spl0;
input_r = spl1;

// Mono conversion (if enabled)
mono_mode ? (
  mono_sum = (input_l + input_r) * 0.5;
  input_l = mono_sum;
  input_r = mono_sum;
);

// Check if we should use FIR direct mode (mode 4 only)
use_fir_direct = (interp_mode == 4) && (target_rate < srate * 0.95);

use_fir_direct ? (
  // ===== FIR BAND-LIMITED MODE: Filter only, no capture =====
  
  // Apply pre-filter if enabled (anti-aliasing before band-limiting)
  prefilter && (slider1_raw < srate * 0.95) ? (
    prefilter == 1 ? (
      // IIR pre-filter
      filtered_l = input_l;
      filtered_r = input_r;
      stage = 1;
      loop(pre_stages,
        filtered_l = filter_stage_lp(filtered_l, 0, stage, 0, nyquist_freq, pre_stages);
        filtered_r = filter_stage_lp(filtered_r, 0, stage, 1, nyquist_freq, pre_stages);
        stage += 1;
      );
    ) : (
      // FIR pre-filter
      filtered_l = fir_lowpass(input_l, fir_pre_buffer_l, nyquist_freq);
      filtered_r = fir_lowpass(input_r, fir_pre_buffer_r, nyquist_freq);
    );
    resampled_l = filtered_l;
    resampled_r = filtered_r;
  ) : (
    resampled_l = input_l;
    resampled_r = input_r;
  );
  
) : (
  // ===== MODES 0-3: Original processing (capture/hold/interpolate) =====
  
  // Step 1: Pre-filter (Anti-aliasing, if enabled)
  prefilter && (slider1_raw < srate * 0.95) ? (
    prefilter == 1 ? (
      filtered_l = input_l;
      filtered_r = input_r;
      stage = 1;
      loop(pre_stages,
        filtered_l = filter_stage_lp(filtered_l, 0, stage, 0, nyquist_freq, pre_stages);
        filtered_r = filter_stage_lp(filtered_r, 0, stage, 1, nyquist_freq, pre_stages);
        stage += 1;
      );
    ) : (
      filtered_l = fir_lowpass(input_l, fir_pre_buffer_l, nyquist_freq);
      filtered_r = fir_lowpass(input_r, fir_pre_buffer_r, nyquist_freq);
    );
  ) : (
    filtered_l = input_l;
    filtered_r = input_r;
  );

  // Step 2: Sample rate reduction with interpolation
  target_rate < srate ? (
    rate_ratio = target_rate / srate;
    phase_accum_l += rate_ratio;
    phase_accum_r += rate_ratio;
    
    phase_accum_l >= 1.0 ? (
      pprev_held_l = prev_held_l;
      prev_held_l = held_l;
      held_l = next_held_l;
      next_held_l = filtered_l;
      phase_accum_l -= 1.0;
    );
    
    phase_accum_r >= 1.0 ? (
      pprev_held_r = prev_held_r;
      prev_held_r = held_r;
      held_r = next_held_r;
      next_held_r = filtered_r;
      phase_accum_r -= 1.0;
    );
    
    // Interpolate based on mode
    interp_mode == 0 ? (
      resampled_l = held_l;
      resampled_r = held_r;
    ) : interp_mode == 1 ? (
      resampled_l = linear_interp(phase_accum_l, prev_held_l, held_l);
      resampled_r = linear_interp(phase_accum_r, prev_held_r, held_r);
    ) : interp_mode == 2 ? (
      resampled_l = cubic_interp(phase_accum_l, pprev_held_l, prev_held_l, held_l, next_held_l);
      resampled_r = cubic_interp(phase_accum_r, pprev_held_r, prev_held_r, held_r, next_held_r);
    ) : (
      // Band-limited IIR mode (mode 3) - just do interpolation here
      (pre_quality >= 2 || bandlimit_quality >= 2) && target_rate < 8000 ? (
        resampled_l = linear_interp(phase_accum_l, prev_held_l, held_l);
        resampled_r = linear_interp(phase_accum_r, prev_held_r, held_r);
      ) : (
        resampled_l = cubic_interp(phase_accum_l, pprev_held_l, prev_held_l, held_l, next_held_l);
        resampled_r = cubic_interp(phase_accum_r, pprev_held_r, prev_held_r, held_r, next_held_r);
      );
    );
  ) : (
    resampled_l = filtered_l;
    resampled_r = filtered_r;
  );
);

// ===== COMMON PROCESSING FOR ALL MODES =====

// Step 3: Dither (before bit crushing)
dither_silence_cutoff ? (
  signal_present = (abs(resampled_l) > 0.00001) || (abs(resampled_r) > 0.00001);
) : (
  signal_present = 1;
);

btcrush && dither_type > 0 && signal_present ? (
  resampled_l = apply_dither(resampled_l, bit_depth, dither_type, dither_amount);
  resampled_r = apply_dither(resampled_r, bit_depth, dither_type, dither_amount);
);

// Step 4: Bit depth crushing
btcrush ? (
  output_l = bit_crush(resampled_l, bit_depth, crushgate);
  output_r = bit_crush(resampled_r, bit_depth, crushgate);
) : (
  output_l = resampled_l;
  output_r = resampled_r;
);

// Step 5: Band-limit reconstruction (filters BOTH resampling AND quantization artifacts)
use_fir_direct ? (
  // FIR mode: Apply FIR lowpass at target Nyquist AFTER bit crushing
  (target_rate < srate * 0.95) ? (
    fir_nyquist = target_rate * 0.5 * 0.98;
    output_l = fir_lowpass(output_l, fir_band_buffer_l, fir_nyquist);
    output_r = fir_lowpass(output_r, fir_band_buffer_r, fir_nyquist);
  );
) : (
  // IIR mode 3: Apply IIR lowpass AFTER bit crushing (this is the fix)
  (interp_mode == 3) && (slider1_raw < srate * 0.95) ? (
    stage = 1;
    loop(bandlimit_stages,
      output_l = filter_stage_lp(output_l, 48, stage, 0, bandlimit_freq, bandlimit_stages);
      output_r = filter_stage_lp(output_r, 48, stage, 1, bandlimit_freq, bandlimit_stages);
      stage += 1;
    );
  );
);

// Step 6: Isolation filter (High-pass to isolate artifacts)
postfilter ? (
  stage = 1;
  loop(isolation_stages,
    output_l = filter_stage_hp(output_l, 96, stage, 0, nyquist_freq, isolation_stages);
    output_r = filter_stage_hp(output_r, 96, stage, 1, nyquist_freq, isolation_stages);
    stage += 1;
  );
);

// Apply output gain
spl0 = output_l * gain;
spl1 = output_r * gain;

// Increment FIR buffer position (only when FIR is actually used)
(prefilter == 2 || use_fir_direct) ? (
  fir_buffer_pos = (fir_buffer_pos + 1) % fir_tap_count;
);
